Hello people. Meet Jack, spirit of Himalayan canines. If you have been to treks you will always find him accompanying you, walking with you, running ahead then coming around, resting when you rest, always looking out for you, as long as he is with you. He is dirty from all the trips he has taken but never tired. He will take another company in a second but will never have a master. He is wild and free but has never betrayed. When you are out of breath and your resolve to reach your destination is wavering by looking at the height of the mountain yet to be climbed, he gives you courage. He is Jack, the canine. .

A blogger committed suicide.
End of a story!
. 
But it wasn’t a suicide it was a murder. Amna Atiq was bullied by fellow women on this hypocrite social media.
.
She used to be very open about her family.
She was depressed 
Sab btati thi 
Kia hua uskay sath
Kon kia karta raha .
Baap nay mother ki death k foren bad nayi shadi disclose ki or bv thi 28 ki jab k wo khud 23 ki thi. Baap ik well known businessman hai.
.
Shadi galat jaga hogayi husband characterless admi tha or beti hogayi. Or uss admi nay divorce kardia.
Uski beti uska ex husband lay gaya because uskay pass beti ko rakhnay k lye finances nahi thay.
Uskay baap nay usko ghar nahi ghusnay dia kyunkay usnay apni marzi ki shadi ko Disown kardia.
Uska husband love marriage k bawajood usko past k taany daita tha. Ghar say bahar nikalny ki ijazat nahi thi.
.
Ye sab or bhi bohat kuch wo openly batati
.
Amna Atiq tragic story teaches us that mental illness is real and it is fatal. When you push people to the edge and torture them both physically and mentally you may not actually kill them but your actions can cause their death.
.
Cases like hers remind us to address the signs of mental illness and ask people if they are okay, if you know about someone who is having a rough period in life TALK to them, you never know your one conversation might have a positive impact.
.
The effects of bullying are tragic and it is clear in amnas case where her own family have caused their death, she didn’t die because of the “patriarchy” or “men” she died because we failed to help and the system failed her.
.
Whatever role her father and husband had in her death they are two sick individuals, you cannot generalise their actions with men worldwide no two people are the same.
.
Before you speak or do anything think about the consequences.
.
‎إِنَّا لِلّهِ وَإِنَّـا إِلَيْهِ رَاجِعون 
May ALLAH ALMIGHTY grant her jannah.
. .

Prime Minister of Pakistan Imran Khan arrives in New York to lead Pakistan delegation at UNGA (20.09.19)
#PrimeMinisterImranKhan #Pakistan 🇵🇰 #USA 🇺🇸 #UnitedNations 🇺🇳 #Kashmir #UNGA

Prime Minister Imran Khan has arrived in New York on a weeklong visit to attend the UN General Assembly session.

On arrival, he was received by Pakistan's UN Permanent representative to UN Maleha Lodhi, Pakistan Ambassador to US and Senior Officials. He will deliver his address to the UN General Assembly on 27th of this month and share Pakistan's perspective and position on the Jammu and Kashmir dispute and its current human rights and related dimensions.

The Prime Minister will also avail the opportunity to articulate Pakistan's perspective on some key contemporary issues.

Imran Khan will hold several bilateral meetings with his counterparts from various regions and participate in high-level UN summits on climate change, sustainable development, universal health coverage and financing for development.

He will also attend and speak at high-level side events co-hosted by Pakistan and Turkey on countering hate speech and on environmental protection and poverty alleviation, co-hosted by Malaysia and Pakistan.

A trilateral summit meeting of Pakistan, Malaysia and Turkey will be held on the General Assembly sidelines.

Apart from these engagements, the Prime Minister will interact with cross-section of international media outlets including meetings with editorial boards.

The Prime Minister's speaking engagements at leading think-tanks and meetings with heads of major international human rights organizations are also envisaged.

Overall, the centrality of the Jammu and Kashmir dispute would be emphasized through myriad engagements.

Foreign Minister Shah Mahmood Qureshi will also attend and address important Ministerial meetings, especially the OIC Contact Group on Jammu and Kashmir.
